problem:
Coplanar squares $ABGH$ and $BCDF$ are adjacent, with $CD = 540298$ units and $AH = 902$ units. Point $E$ is on segments $AD$ and $GB$. What is the area of triangle $ABE$, in square units? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(902,0)--(902,902)--(0,902)--(0,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));
draw((902,0)--(541200,0)--(541200,540298)--(902,540298)--(902,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));

draw((0,0)--(541200,540298),linewidth(2));

filldraw((0,0)--(902,0)--(902,540298/600)--(0,0)--cycle,gray,linewidth(2));

label("A",(0,0),SW);
label("B",(902,0),S);
label("C",(541200,0),SE);
label("D",(541200,540298),NE);
label("E",(902,540298/600),SE);
label("F",(902,540298),NW);
label("G",(902,902),NW);
label("H",(0,902),NW);
[/asy]
